The paper deals with methods of transforming possibility distributions into probability intervals, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The use of Sugeno and Choquet integrals is also mentioned, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and decision making (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with uncertainty and probability, which are also relevant topics in systems and control theory (cs.SI).
